events.name: OK Google: Build Interactive Apps with Google Assistant
events.description:
With Google Assistant expected to be part of over a billion consumer devices by the end of this year, this Quest teaches you how to build practical Google Assistant applications integrated with Google Cloud services via APIs. Example apps will use the Dialogflow conversational suite and the Actions and Cloud Functions frameworks.

No hardware required -- these labs use the cloud-based Google Assistant simulator environment for developing and testing -- but if you do have your own device, such as a Google Home or a Google Hub, additional instructions are provided on how to deploy your apps to your own hardware.

Meeting ID: meet.google.com/dvh-dqaf-dhf

events.name: A Tour of Qwiklabs and the Google Cloud Platform
events.description:
The Google Cloud Platform (GCP) is a suite of cloud services hosted on Google's infrastructure. From computing and storage, to data analytics, machine learning, and networking, GCP offers a wide variety of services and APIs that can be integrated with any cloud-computing application or project—be it personal or enterprise-grade.

In this introductory-level lab, you will take your first steps with GCP by getting hands-on practice with the Google Cloud Platform console—an in-browser UI that lets you access and manage Google Cloud services. You will identify key features of GCP and also learn the ins and outs of the Qwiklabs environment. If you are new to cloud computing or looking for an overview of GCP and Qwiklabs, you are in the right place. Read on to learn about the specifics of this lab and areas that you will get hands-on practice with.

Meeting ID: https://meet.google.com/nfg-fcvw-ppk

events.name: Cloud Study Jam: A Tour of Qwiklabs and the Google Cloud Platform
events.description:
Note - This event is going to be online only now. It will be streamed on YouTube Live. Based on latest guidelines provided by Health Canada we want to avoid gathering of more than 15 people.

Please join us at https://youtu.be/fHG3AVvicc4

The event is supported by Faculty of Applied Science & Technology, Sheridan College and conducted by GDG Mississauga.

We will have Head of Google North America, Developer Ecosystem speaking at this event. It will be a great opportunity to come out and network.

This workshop provides a basic overview of Cloud Computing using the Google Cloud Platform. This includes launching, resizing, managing and monitoring a Virtual Machine Instance.

Please Note: As this event is a hands-on session, attendees must keep their own laptops and chargers.

Takeaways for the day

1. Complete the 'Introduction to Google Cloud Platform' and ‘Creating
a Virtual Machine’ Lab.
2. Qwiklab credits will be provided to the participants.
3. Exciting Giveaways.

Agenda:
12:00 PM - 12:15 PM: Introductions
12.15 PM - 1.00 PM: LAB Setup, Hands-on Lab - 'Introduction to Google Cloud Platform'
1: 00 PM - 1:30 PM: Networking
1:30 PM - 2.30 PM: Hands-on Lab ‘Creating a Virtual Machine’
2:30 PM - 3:00 PM Speaker: Head of Google North America, Developer Ecosystem, Swag Giveaways and Wrap Up

**Credits for the Lab will be provided during the Workshop.
